id: pm-z3ez
title: "Agent distribution funnel: MCP Registry record, canonical portable Agent Skills, pm setup-agent, pm agent doctor, agent project profile, version-coherent plugins"
description: "Marketing to agents is product distribution: agents discover and select tools through registry records, tool/skill metadata, repo guidance, trust metadata, and context cost — not blog posts. Build the machine-facing acquisition funnel on existing assets (pm-mcp binary, Claude/Codex skills, profile system, health/doctor infrastructure)."
type: Feature
status: open
priority: 1
tags[5]: agents,distribution,mcp,onboarding,skills
created_at: "2026-07-13T09:31:21.359Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-13T09:31:45.826Z"
author: maintainer-agent
estimated_minutes: 1200
acceptance_criteria: "pm-mcp published to the official MCP Registry with verified namespace, version-pinned launch command, transports, runtime requirement, permissions/local-data behavior; one canonical portable Agent Skills source tree derives the Claude and Codex skill packages (no hand-maintained copies) with trigger-oriented descriptions plus positive and near-miss trigger tests; pm setup-agent <client|all> detects the client, installs/updates skills, configures version-pinned MCP, selects a tool profile, verifies handshake, and runs a read-only pm context smoke test; pm agent doctor verifies runtime, workspace discovery, MCP launch, profile, skill/plugin versions, contract compatibility, context read, token size, and mutation identity; an agent project profile (pm profile apply agent) composes pm-brief, pm-context, compact context depth, search defaults, and minimal guidance; generated repository guidance stays tiny (a few pm commands + contracts pointer, detail lives in skills/pm guide); Codex plugin never silently runs a newer @latest MCP server than the installed plugin (bundle, pin, or fail clearly — same class as pm-l9wl on the Claude side)"
parent: pm-wjfa
risk: medium
confidence: medium
dependencies[1]{id,kind,created_at,author,source_kind}:
  pm-l9wl,related,"2026-07-13T09:31:21.359Z",null,null
body: "# Agent distribution funnel\n\nHumans discover via posts/demos/search. Agents discover and select via: tool names+descriptions, skill metadata, repository instructions, MCP registry records, resources/prompts, trust+permission metadata, context cost, and successful prior calls. Funnel stages:\n\n    DISCOVERY  registry, package metadata, agent skill, AGENTS.md, plugin marketplace\n    SELECTION  tool description quality, trigger accuracy, small active surface, trust metadata\n    ACTIVATION workspace detection, init, health/doctor, first context result\n    VALUE      correct next work, successful claim, useful handoff, evidence-backed close\n    RETENTION  session hook, durable history, new-session continuity, low context cost\n\n## Canonical Agent Skills package (derive Claude + Codex from ONE source tree, portable SKILL.md format)\nRecommended skills and triggers: pm-orient (starting/resuming work in a pm repository) · pm-triage (turning a request into duplicate-checked structured work) · pm-plan (creating/updating a durable implementation plan) · pm-deliver (claim, implement, link evidence, validate, close) · pm-handoff (compact context for another agent/session) · pm-review (health, duplicates, missing metadata, project integrity checks) · pm-package-author (building/testing a pm SDK package). Each skill: precise trigger-oriented description (optimized for triggering, not marketing prose), explicit use-when / do-not-use-when boundaries, short core procedure, on-demand references, positive trigger tests, near-miss negative tests, output-quality evals. Example description: \"Use when starting, resuming, triaging, planning, implementing, verifying, or handing off repository work managed under .agents/pm. Prefer pm context, pm next, and search before creating or mutating items.\"\n\n## MCP Registry (preview — keep editor-specific setup paths too)\nCanonical record: stable package identifier, version-pinned launch command, supported transports, runtime requirement, tool profiles, permissions + local-data behavior, repo/docs metadata, checksums/provenance where supported. Verify the namespace.\n\n## MCP resources and prompts (reduce pressure to make every behavior a tool)\nResources: pm://workspace/context, pm://workspace/contracts, pm://workspace/schema, pm://workflow/orient, pm://workflow/deliver, pm://workflow/handoff, pm://packages/catalog. Prompts: pm-start-work, pm-triage-request, pm-create-plan, pm-close-with-evidence, pm-handoff.\n\n## pm setup-agent (build on existing pm init --agent-guidance, do not replace it)\n    pm setup-agent claude|codex|cursor|vscode|gemini|windsurf|all\n1 detect client, 2 install/update canonical skills, 3 configure MCP with version-pinned runtime, 4 add minimal repo guidance, 5 select default tool profile, 6 verify handshake + tool list, 7 read-only pm context smoke test, 8 print exact next steps.\n\n## pm agent doctor (support tool AND onboarding conversion tool)\n    pm agent doctor [--client claude|codex] [--json]\nChecks: runtime version, workspace discovery, MCP launch, tool profile, skill install+version, plugin/runtime compatibility, package activation, contract compatibility, context read, token size, mutation identity, optional search-provider health. Builds on existing health/validate/package-doctor infrastructure.\n\n## agent project profile (use the existing profile system — profiles already compose schema, workflows, config, templates, recommended packages)\n`pm profile apply agent`: recommends pm-brief + pm-context + guide-shell + linked-test adapters, agent-oriented workflow defaults, compact context depth, search defaults, minimal guidance. Advanced semantic search stays optional.\n\n## Tiny repository guidance (generated; giant AGENTS.md files are an anti-goal — fence note (4) on pm-wjfa)\n    ## Project context\n    This repository uses pm.\n    - Start with pm context --limit 10 or pm next.\n    - Search before creating work. Claim before mutating.\n    - Link relevant files, docs, and tests. Close with evidence and a reason.\n    - pm contracts --summary --json for the active machine surface.\n\n## Version coherence\nThe Codex plugin must not silently run a newer @latest MCP server than the installed plugin: bundle the matching runtime, pin the npm version in generated launcher metadata, resolve the plugin version and request exactly it, or fail clearly. Claude-side marketplace @latest fallback is owned by pm-l9wl (related) — fix per-plugin, same class. Version coherence is part of the trust story."
